name: GEO_BENE_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ASSIGNED SURROGATE KEY USED TO IDENTIFY A BENEFICIARYS ZIP CODE, AND ESTABLISHES UNIQUENESS OF A CLAIM. THIS IS A COMPONENT OF THE CLAIM 4 AND 5-PART KEYS USED FOR JOINING CLAIMS.

name: CLM_DT_SGNTR_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ASSIGNED SURROGATE KEY IDENTIFYING A DISTINCT COMBINATION OF RELATED DATES USED TO ESTABLISH UNIQUENESS OF A CLAIM. THE DISTINCT COMBINATION OF DATE GROUPINGS IS A COMPONENT OF THE CLAIM 4 AND 5-PART KEYS.

name: CLM_TYPE_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE SOURCE AND TYPE OF CLAIM SUBMITTED THROUGH THE MEDICARE OR MEDICAID PROGRAM.  FOR EXAMPLE:  60 = MEDICARE  NATIONAL CLAIMS HISTORY (NCH) INPATIENT CLAIM   8900 = MEDICAID FEE FOR SERVICE DENTAL     REFERENCE TABLE: CLM_TYPE_CD

name: CLM_NUM_SK
comment: AN INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) ASSIGNED SURROGATE KEY USED TO DIFFERENTIATE CLAIMS THAT HAVE COMMON GEOGRAPHY, CLAIM DATES AND CLAIM TYPES. WHEN THE SAME COMBINATION OF GEO_BENE_SK, CLM_DT_SGNTR_SK, AND CLM_TYPE_CD IS NOT UNIQUE, THE CLM_NUM_SK IS SEQUENCED TO MAKE THE 4 AND 5 PART KEYS UNIQUE.  THIS IS A COMPONENT OF THE CLAIM 4 AND 5-PART KEYS USED FOR JOINING CLAIMS.

name: CLM_LINE_NUM
comment: A NUMBER IDENTIFYING THE POSITION OF THE SERVICE OR ITEM ON THE CLAIM. THIS IS A COMPONENT OF THE 5-PART KEY USED FOR JOINING CLAIMS.

name: CLM_LINE_FPS_RMRK_CD
comment: AN AMERICAN NATIONAL STANDARD INSTITUTE (ANSI) REMITTANCE ADVICE REMARK CODE (RARC) PROVIDING ADDITIONAL EXPLANATIONS FOR AN ADJUSTMENT ALREADY DESCRIBED BY A CLAIM ADJUSTMENT REASON CODE (CARC) OR TO CONVEY INFORMATION ABOUT REMITTANCE PROCESSING THAT IS NOT RELATED TO A SPECIFIC ADJUSTMENT OR CARC.    FOR EXAMPLE:  M2 = NOT PAID SEPARATELY WHEN THE PATIENT IS AN INPATIENT.  N395 = MISSING LABORATORY REPORT.    REFERENCE TABLE: CLM_RMTNC_ADVC_RMRK_CD

name: CLM_LINE_FPS_RSN_CD
comment: AN AMERICAN NATIONAL STANDARDS INSTITUTE (ANSI) CLAIM ADJUSTMENT REASON CODE (CARC) IDENTIFYING THE REASON FOR AN ADJUSTMENT TO A CLAIM OR SERVICE LINE THAT RESULTED IN A DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THE ORIGINAL BILLED AMOUNT AND THE FINAL PAID AMOUNT. AN ADJUSTMENT CAN RESULT IN A DENIAL, REDUCTION, OR INCREASE  IN PAYMENT.  FOR EXAMPLE:  1 = DEDUCTIBLE AMOUNT  B1 = NON-COVERED VISITS    REFERENCE TABLE: CLM_ADJSTMT_RSN_CD

name: CLM_LINE_QMB_SW
comment: A SWITCH INDICATING WHETHER A BENEFICIARY IS ENROLLED IN THE QUALIFIED MEDICARE BENEFICIARY (QMB) PROGRAM.               VALID VALUES:  Y = THE BENEFICIARY IS ENROLLED IN THE QMB PROGRAM  N = THE BENEFICIARY IS NOT ENROLLED IN THE QMB PROGRAM

name: CLM_LINE_PBID_SW
comment: A SWITCH INDICATING WHETHER A BENEFICIARY IS ENROLLED IN THE PART B IMMUNOSUPPRESSIVE DRUG (PBID) PROGRAM.                                                        VALID VALUES:  Y = THE BENEFICIARY IS ENROLLED IN THE PBID PROGRAM  N = THE BENEFICIARY IS NOT ENROLLED IN THE PBID PROGRAM

name: CLM_SNCTN_SW
comment: A SWITCH INDICATING WHEN A SUPPLIER OR PROVIDER IS SANCTIONED BY THE OFFICE OF THE INSPECTOR GENERAL (OIG).                                                                         VALID VALUES:  Y =PROVIDER IS SANCTIONED  N= PROVIDER IS NOT SANCTIONED

name: CLM_LINE_DEMO_PRCNG_CD
comment: A CODE IDENTIFYING THE DEMONSTRATION MODEL USED FOR PRICING ON A CLAIM LINE.    REFERENCE TABLE:  CLM_LINE_DEMO_PRCNG_CD

name: CLM_LINE_ACO_ID_NUM
comment: A NUMBER IDENTIFYING THE ACCOUNTABLE CARE ORGANIZATION (ACO) FOR A CLAIM LINE.

name: CLM_LINE_ACO_RDCTN_PCT
comment: A PERCENTAGE INDICATING THE ACCOUNTABLE CARE ORGANIZATION (ACO) REDUCTION APPLIED TO A CLAIM LINE.

name: CLM_LINE_MOLDX_TEST_ID
comment: A UNIQUE IDENTIFIER ASSIGNED TO MOLECULAR DIAGNOSTIC TESTS (MDT) THAT PROVIDES A CROSSWALK TO A TESTS DETAILED INFORMATION ON FILE WHEN SUBMITTED FOR REIMBURSEMENT UNDER THE MOLECULAR DIAGNOSTIC SERVICES (MOLDX) PROGRAM.

name: CLM_LINE_QPP_ADJSTMT_AMT
comment: AN AMOUNT REPRESENTING A QUALITY PAYMENT PROGRAM (QPP) ADJUSTMENT THAT HAS BEEN APPLIED FOR AN ELIGIBLE CLINICIAN PARTICIPATING IN THE MERIT BASED INCENTIVE PAYMENT SYSTEM (MIPS) PROGRAM.

name: CLM_LINE_QPP_ADJSTMT_CD
comment: A CODE INDICATING THE TYPE OF QUALITY PAYMENT PROGRAM (QPP) ADJUSTMENT APPLIED TO A PAID AMOUNT FOR AN ELIGIBLE CLINICIAN PARTICIPATING IN THE MERIT BASED INCENTIVE PAYMENT SYSTEM (MIPS) PROGRAM.  VALID VALUES:  P = POSITIVE (BONUS)  N = NEGATIVE (PENALTY)  ~ = DEFAULT

name: CLM_LINE_QPP_ADJSTMT_PCT
comment: A VALUE IDENTIFYING THE QUALITY PAYMENT PROGRAM (QPP) ADJUSTMENT PERCENTAGE APPLIED TO A PAID AMOUNT FOR AN ELIGIBLE CLINICIAN PARTICIPATING IN THE MERIT BASED INCENTIVE PAYMENT SYSTEM (MIPS) PROGRAM.

name: CLM_LINE_SNF_PDPM_AMT
comment: AN AMOUNT REPRESENTING A PAYMENT BASED ON THE SKILLED NURSING FACILITY (SNF) PROSPECTIVE PAYMENT SYSTEM (PPS) UNDER THE PATIENT DRIVEN PAYMENT MODEL (PDPM).

name: CLM_LINE_MODEL_REIMBRSMT_AMT
comment: AN AMOUNT REPRESENTING THE ACTUAL AMOUNT MEDICARE WOULD HAVE PAID FOR THE CLAIM LINE IN THE ABSENCE OF GLOBAL BUDGET PAYMENTS MADE UNDER A DEMONSTRATION MODEL.   NOTE: AT THIS TIME, THIS IS ONLY APPLICABLE TO THE PENNSYLVANIA RURAL HEALTH MODEL (PARHM).

name: CLM_LINE_MDPCP_RDCTN_AMT
comment: AN AMOUNT IDENTIFYING THE REDUCED LINE LEVEL PAYMENT FOR A FEDERALLY QUALIFIED HEALTH CENTER (FQHC) PARTICIPANT IN THE MARYLAND PRIMARY CARE PROGRAM (MDPCP) DEMONSTRATION MODEL.

name: CLM_LINE_PTOT_ASTNT_RDCTN_AMT
comment: AN AMOUNT IDENTIFYING THE REDUCED LINE LEVEL PAYMENT FOR OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY AND PHYSICAL THERAPY SERVICES FURNISHED IN WHOLE OR IN PART BY PHYSICAL THERAPIST ASSISTANTS (PTAS) OR OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY ASSISTANTS (OTAS).  EFFECTIVE JANUARY 3, 2023, THIS FIELD WILL INCLUDE THE RURAL EMERGENCY HOSPITAL (REH) 5% PAYMENT INCREASE. APPLIES TO CLAIMS PROCESSED BY THE OUTPATIENT PROSPECTIVE PAYMENT SYSTEM (OPPS), IDENTIFIED BY PROVIDER TYPE OF Ñ²4Ò¬ CLM-OPPS-IND = 2, AND TOBS 13X AND 14X.

name: CLM_LINE_MDPCP_RDCTN_PCT
comment: A PERCENTAGE INDICATING THE REDUCTION TAKEN ON A MARYLAND PRIMARY CARE PROGRAM (MDPCP) DEMONSTRATION CLAIM.

name: CLM_LINE_MDPCP_TRK_3_FVF_AMT
comment: AN AMOUNT IDENTIFYING THE FLAT VISIT FEE (FVF) APPLIED ON A TRACK 3 MARYLAND PRIMARY CARE PROGRAM (MDPCP) DEMONSTRATION CLAIM.

name: CLM_LINE_COINSRNC_PCT
comment: A VALUE IDENTIFYING THE COINSURANCE PERCENTAGE APPLIED TO THE SERVICE AT THE CLAIM LINE.

name: META_SK
comment: A UNIQUE LEGACY NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR), FORMULATED WITH A DATE AND A 3-DIGIT SEQUENCE NUMBER, WHICH IDENTIFIES THE BATCH PROCESS THAT INITIALLY LOADED A ROW IN THE IDR. DUE TO THE LIMITATION OF A 3-DIGIT VALUE, THIS IS BEING REPLACED BY META_SRC_PRCSG_ID ON NEW IDR TABLES AS THE SOURCE DATA TRACKING STANDARD.

name: META_SRC_PRCSG_ID
comment: A VALUE ASSIGNED BASED ON A BATCH IDENTIFICATION IN ORDER TO TRACE IT BACK TO ITS ORIGINAL SOURCE. IT WILL ONLY BE POPULATED WHEN A RECORD IS INSERTED.

name: META_LST_UPDT_SK
comment: AN IDR ASSIGNED SURROGATE KEY USED TO IDENTIFY THE BATCH PROCESS THAT LOADED OR LAST UPDATED A ROW, WHICHEVER OCCURRED LAST.

name: META_LST_UPDT_SRC_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) USED TO IDENTIFY THE SPECIFIC SOURCE OF THE DATA WHEN A ROW IS LOADED INTO THE IDR.    REFERENCE TABLE: V2_MDCR_META_DCTNRY_SRC

name: META_SRC_SK
comment: A UNIQUE NUMERIC VALUE ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) USED TO IDENTIFY THE SPECIFIC SOURCE OF THE DATA WHEN A ROW IS LOADED INTO THE IDR.    REFERENCE TABLE: V2_MDCR_META_DCTNRY_SRC

name: META_LTST_SRC_PRCSG_ID
comment: A VALUE ASSIGNED BASED ON A BATCH IDENTIFICATION IN ORDER TO TRACE IT BACK TO ITS ORIGINAL SOURCE. IT WILL ONLY BE POPULATED WHEN A RECORD IS SUBSEQUENTLY UPDATED.

name: IDR_INSRT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHILE PERFORMING AN INSERT OPERATION.

name: IDR_UPDT_TS
comment: THE SYSTEM DATE AND TIME ASSIGNED BY THE INTEGRATED DATA REPOSITORY (IDR) WHEN UPDATES ARE MADE TO ANY NON-PRIMARY KEY COLUMN.
